  "title": {
    "en": "God Calls Moses"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "Years after Jacob’s family settled in Egypt, their descendants were oppressed.",
      "God sees their suffering and calls Moses to lead them."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "call",
        "icon": "local_fire_department",
        "label": { "en": "God Calls His Name" },
        "lines": [
          "God called to him,",
          "“Moses! Moses!”",
          "And Moses said,",
          "“Here I am.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "compassion",
        "icon": "visibility",
        "label": { "en": "God Sees and Hears" },
        "lines": [
          "“Now the cry of the Israelites has reached me,",
          "and I have seen the way",
          "the Egyptians are oppressing them.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "mission",
        "icon": "send",
        "label": { "en": "Sent to Pharaoh" },
        "lines": [
          "“So now, go.",
          "I am sending you to Pharaoh",
          "to bring my people the Israelites",
          "out of Egypt.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about God’s awareness of suffering and His choice to send Moses?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Exodus 3:1–10"]
  }
}
